author: @Chery_sw
text:
No creo que tenga mucho sentido comparar este stage con el de Le sserafim. En primer lugar, el entrenamiento de Blackpink fue más largo y en este momento llevaban muchos años de experiencia. Es como comparar un árbol que lleva creciendo 10 años y uno que lleva creciendo 1 años. Es evidente que no van a ser iguales. Igualmente la gente puede comparar ambos grupos, pero objetivamente no tiene sentido.

Además, en el caso de YG las coreografias son mucho mas asequibles. No sé en qué piensa Hybe dándole a Le sserafim coreografías como si fueran para un concurso de baile. No es realista en absoluto. Estoy harta de ese tipo de coreografías en detrimento de un buen permormance vocal (no solo en el caso de le sserafim, el 90% de los grupos actuales son así).

text: ar 얘기 하는 사람들 넘 웃김.. ar이랑 라이브 목소리 2개가 확실하게 나뉘어서 들려서 라이브감이 살아있다는 게 사람들이 감탄하는 부분인데; 중간에 제니 호응유도하기 직전 부분이나 마지막 댄.브 때는 ar만 나오는데 딱 이 정도 크기로 깔려 있고 그외는 멤버들 목소리가 확실하게 2개로 들리고 심지어 원곡이상으로 잘함. 23년도 블랙핑크 콘서트 다녀왔는데 체감으로는 멤버들 전부 이 영상보다 훨씬 쩌렁쩌렁할 정도로 성량큼. 목소리 층이 2개로 구분안되고 중간중간 숨소리 넣은 ar만 트는(혹은 이런 ar 조차 뚫지 못하는 성량을 가진) 공연을 하는 팀의 팬들이 꼭 ar깔렸으니 생라아니잖아! 우리랑 똑같아! < 이럼. 콘서트 직캠만 비교해봐도 차이나는데..  목소리 층 구분 없이 이게 생라이브인가  ar인가? 하고 생각하게 되면 그냥 ar만 튼 경우가 많고 ar이랑 목소리가 2개로 구분해서 들리면 댄스라이브니까 깔아두긴 했구나 정도로 생각할 수 있는 건데 이 차이를 모름. 그리고 댄스라이브는  파트 사이 숨 조절을 위해 끝부분은 날리는 경우도 있는데 이걸로 립싱크야! 이럼 ㅋㅋ 블핑은 누구들처럼 파트 놓친 게 아니라 숨조절 위한 부분은 대놓고 안 부르는  거 보여주는데.. 이러니까 그런 가수들의 콘서트에 가서 라이브라 좋았어~ 하고 돈 버리고 오는 건가 싶고

text:
Aku kesini setelah melihat grup yang tampil di coachella kemarin, aku takut jari-jariku menyakiti mereka, tapi kita tidak bisa menutup mata akan ini. Jika fans mereka bilang "vocal tidak maksimal karena tarian", maka mereka bisa mengurangi power tariannya dan menaikkan power vocalnya (bukankah mereka punya penari latar?). Sebagai penikmat lagu sekaligus seorang penggemar kpop, menurutku, seorang penyanyi harus bisa menyanyi dan seorang dancer harus bisa menari.

Belajar dari Blackpink, blackpink membawakan lagu mereka dengan baik diacara ini bahkan aespa juga bisa.

Ah entahlah, aku bingung mau bicara apa lagi.

author: @ivyagnorroadto1ksubs234
text:
Queens literally SLAYED.Just, SLAYYY.
But I really think YG is overtraining the girls and really should give them some rest. 
As most of the blinks might know, first jisoo was infected with Covid-19 and in the recent Melbourne concert Jennie tried so hard to perform but her body just couldn’t. 
But Jennie still pushed herself to perform and tried her best.
And Lisa and rose are also not very well.
Whoever agree with me please like.
And don’t think that I’m doing this for the likes, I just wanna see how many ppl agree with me and support BLACKPINK truly.
I’m sorry if I’ve said something that has hurt someone.I don’t mean it I’m just giving my opinion.




Another thing, y’all might have heard a lot of blinks saying “we wanted to see Jennie” , “money wasted”, etc etc. So those who have said these stuff , please don’t call yourself a blink. You should appreciate Jennie that she tried so much to perform and do the concert but her body didn’t support. And they all are also human, they need some rest and instead of attacking Jennie, you should attack YG for being so cruel and not caring abt their health. 
We should spread this talk, YG needs to know to give the girls some rest instead of doing the concert with 3 members. Just give the girls some rest.
YG is adding more and more concerts after the coachella performance.

Like who all agree with me.
And again please don’t think I’m doing it for the likes, I just wanna see how many ppl agree with me and ACTUALLY support BLACKPINK.


Edit:Guess BLACKPINK does not have any real fans called “BLINKS”

Blackpink (Korean: 블랙핑크; RR: Beullaekpingkeu, stylized in all caps or as BLɅϽKPIИK) is a South Korean girl group formed by YG Entertainment, consisting of members Jisoo, Jennie, Rosé, and Lisa. The group debuted in August 2016 with their single album Square One, which featured "Whistle" and "Boombayah", their first number-one entries on South Korea's Gaon Digital Chart and the US Billboard World Digital Song Sales chart, respectively.

Kim Ji-soo (Korean: 김지수; born January 3, 1995), known mononymously as Jisoo, is a South Korean singer and actress. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Blackpink, formed by YG Entertainment, in August 2016. Outside of her music career, she made her acting debut with a cameo role in the 2015 series The Producers and played her first leading role in the JTBC series Snowdrop (2021–22), for which she won a Seoul International Drama Award.

Jennie Kim (Korean: 김제니; born January 16, 1996), known mononymously as Jennie, is a South Korean singer and rapper. Born and raised in South Korea, Jennie studied in New Zealand for five years before returning to South Korea in 2010. She debuted as a member of the girl group Blackpink, formed by YG Entertainment, in August 2016. In November 2018, Jennie made her debut as a solo artist with the single "Solo". The song was commercially successful, topping both the Gaon Digital Chart and Billboard's World Digital Songs chart. In 2023, she will be making her acting debut in the HBO series The Idol, under the stage name Jennie Ruby Jane.

Roseanne Park (born 11 February 1997), known mononymously as Rosé (Korean: 로제), is a Korean-New Zealand singer and dancer based in South Korea. Born in New Zealand and raised in Australia, Rosé signed with South Korean label YG Entertainment following a successful audition in 2012 and trained for four years before debuting as a member of the girl group Blackpink in August 2016.

Lalisa Manobal (also spelled Manoban; born Pranpriya Manobal; March 27, 1997), known mononymously as Lisa, is a Thai rapper, singer and dancer. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Blackpink, which debuted under YG Entertainment in 2016.
